# Records — one-line immutable data classes

## Kill the data-class boilerplate

```java
public record User(String email, String name, int age) {}
```

- For free: **canonical ctor**, one accessor per component (`email()`),
  `equals`/`hashCode`/`toString`, **final** fields (immutable)

## Still flexible

- Add methods, **validate in a compact constructor**, implement interfaces
- Can't add **mutable state** — the whole point

```java
public Money { if (amountCents < 0) throw ...; }
```
